<B>__{tsavo.}
<A>__{we have arrived at the train station area and what we see is a place that is still being built. there are tin shacks; a water tower is under construction men are working everywhere, for that's what tsavo is: a place for work. the train goes slower still. no one stands idly around here. but no one looks happy either. one man is apart from the rest: this is samuel. an ageless masai, tall and slender, he has a smile that can light the world.}
